I just read the Initiative, by Asphalt. It's a cute little piece with intimate and sexy lewd scenes. I like it. A couple of pointers:
The dialogue can be too on the nose.
>"Mind that you're a giant wolf-lady whos head is longer than my forearm?"
comes off a bit cocky for someone who bitched out of making the first move. It rubbed me the wrong way.
>"I-I can tell that you don't m-mind... w-well... uh.."
I hate it when people do the 'repeat the first letter' thing to indicate a character is stammering or stuttering, it's a lazy and inaccurate shorthand. I'm a stumbling mumbling little fuck in real life, and what you usually see when people stutter is filler words (um, like, so), pauses between words, and repeating words or sentence fragments as you try to figure out what you actually want to say. It's a product of speaking too fast for your mind to keep up.
I also think it's pretty weird that she got really nervous over taking him to the side, especially after getting applauded for a pretty big show of dominance. I get that different people get scared of different things, but that felt off.
All in all though, worthwhile read. Check it out.
